{{Han etym}}
{{zh-etym-double|辛|}}, hence two chisels or knives to mark prisoners, to indicate "recriminate/accuse; quarrel; debate". Perhaps the two chisels symbolize two prisoners accusing each other. {{attention|zh|the Japanese page cites some works, according to which this glyph origin is an incorrect analysis by Shuowen and that based on bronze inscriptions this character is instead a duplication of 䇂 (jade pieces)}}

